- Use `npm install next-auth` to install NextAuth.js.
- Configure Google OAuth in your project by adding the following to `[...nextauth].js`:
  ```javascript
  export default NextAuth({
    providers: [
      GoogleProvider({
        clientId: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID,
        clientSecret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET,
      }),
    ],
  });
  ```
- Set environment variables `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` in your `.env.local`.
- Use the `[...nextauth].js` route to handle authentication callbacks.
- For production, ensure you use HTTPS and configure CORS appropriately.
